  "title": "Senior C&S Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>(A) Job Summary:</p>\n<p>The Senior C&amp;S Coordinator oversees and coordinates civil and structural works for LTA projects, with a focus on roadworks and tunnel construction. The role ensures that works are executed in line with design, safety, and quality standards while supporting smooth progress and compliance with authority requirements.</p>\n<p>(B) Essential Job Functions:</p>\n<p>The Senior C&amp;S Coordinator is responsible, but not limited to, the following:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Coordinate and supervise civil and structural activities for roadworks, tunnels, and related infrastructure.</li>\n  <li>Review drawings, method statements, and shop drawings to ensure compliance with LTA and project specifications.</li>\n  <li>Monitor construction progress and site activities to meet schedule, quality, and safety targets.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with consultants, subcontractors, and relevant authorities to resolve technical and coordination issues.</li>\n  <li>Assist in planning and sequencing of road and tunnel works to minimize disruption and ensure integration with other trades.</li>\n  <li>Support inspections, testing, and approvals by consultants and authorities.</li>\n  <li>Maintain site documentation including reports, permits, and as-built records.</li>\n  <li>Any ad-hoc tasks as assigned by the Superior.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>(C) Minimum Qualifications/ Job Experience:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma / Degree in Civil or Structural Engineering or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Have minimum 8 years of design experience in buildings / stations, at-grade services such as road, drainage &amp; sewerage. </li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of civil, structural, and underground construction methods.</li>\n  <li>Good communication and coordination skills with consultants, subcontractors, and site teams.</li>\n</ul>",
